name: Sarajevo City Hall
description: {'Information': ['Sarajevo City Hall (Vijećnica) is one of the most important and visually stunning landmarks in Sarajevo. Built between 1891 and 1896, it was originally designed to house the city’s municipal government. Its construction represents a significant period during the Austro-Hungarian Empire’s rule over Bosnia and Herzegovina, and the building’s design combines elements of Neo-Moorish and Ottoman styles, which were prominent at the time.'], 'Historical Importance': ["Built in 1896, the City Hall is a symbol of the city's cultural heritage, reflecting the Austro-Hungarian architectural style."], 'Key Features': ['The building features Moorish Revival architecture, intricate stonework, stained glass windows, and a large central hall. It was severely damaged during the Bosnian War but has since been restored.'], 'Working Hours': ['Open daily from 9 AM to 6 PM, but may vary depending on events and holidays.']}
short_description: An architectural gem and historical landmark, now housing a cultural museum.

description: {'Information': ['The Latin Bridge is a historical Ottoman bridge over the Miljacka River in Sarajevo.'], 'Historical Importance': ['It is famous as the site of the assassination of Archduke Franz Ferdinand in 1914, an event that triggered World War I.'], 'Key Features': ['The bridge has a beautiful Ottoman architectural style and offers picturesque views of the Miljacka River and the city.'], 'Working Hours': ['Open year-round; accessible at any time, though the museum nearby has specific hours.']}

name: Mount Igman
